## 5. Time Scrubber Component

From mms-components-research.md, recommended stack:

### 5.1 Architecture

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                     DENSITY VISUALIZATION                        │
│  ▓▓▓▓▒▒▒▓▓▓▓▓▓▓▒▒▒▒▓▓▓▓▓▓▒▒▒▓▓▓▓▓▓▓▒▒▒▓▓▓▓▓▓▓▓▓▓▓▓▓▓▓▓▓▓▓▓▓    │
│  |=====[============VISIBLE RANGE==============]=====|          │
│  2024                    2028                        2036       │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### 5.2 Technology Choices

| Component | Library | Rationale |
|-----------|---------|-----------|
| Density chart | uPlot | 100K pts/ms performance |
| Brush handles | d3-brush | Maximum flexibility |
| Range slider | BlueprintJS RangeSlider | UI consistency |
| GPU filtering | deck.gl DataFilterExtension | Real-time 60K points |

### 5.3 Downsampling

Use LTTB (Largest-Triangle-Three-Buckets) for overview:
- Input: 60,000 tasks
- Output: 500 points for overview chart
- Visual fidelity preserved (97.7% reduction)

